    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Adventurer's Armory 2 pg. 9</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 20 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 4 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> 19-20/x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> S; <strong>Special</strong> distracting, see text</p><p><strong>Category</strong> One-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Blades, Heavy</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>Favored by those residents of Irrisen with no talent for witchcraft, this exotic blade curves multiple times along its 3-1/2 feet. The sickle-sword's hilt is long and curved, and its blade bears a small secondary grip partway up its length. These allow a wielder with a free hand to rapidly twist the sword in unpredictable ways. When wielding a sickle-sword in one hand and nothing in the other, you can spend a swift action to gain a +2 bonus on your next attack roll before the end of your turn.</p>",
